commitResults.messageTitle: Update Glossary and user stories in DG
Add Matriculation Number field to 'Add' command
commitResults.messageBody:
Matriculation Number is one of the fields that will be
contained within a Person object. It will be used for
other functions later to search for students.

This commit amends the 'Add' and 'Edit' command, 'Person'
class and other relevant classes and tests to support
the use of the Matriculation Number parameter to keep
track of students.

Since the Matriculation Number for every student is unique, it
reduces the need for UHC staff to distinguish between students
with similar names.

I had forgotten to include this file in the
previous commit.

Vaccination Status is one of the fields that will be contained
within a Person object. It will be used to,

*Determine if students require a vaccination if they are not already
vaccinated.
*Determine the proportion of students who have already been vaccinated.

This commit amends the 'Add' and 'Edit' command, 'Person' class and
other relevant classes and tests to support the use of the Vaccination
Status parameter.

The Vaccination Status will allow UHC staff to contact un-vaccinated
students more quickly, and inform NUS management if further reopenings
are possible and safe.

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove Tag, add MedicalDetails parameter in 'Add'
commitResults.messageBody:
The 'Tag' field is a legacy of the original AB3 code. It will not be
used in Vax@NUS. Medical Details is one of the fields that will be
contained within a Person object. It will be used to determine if a
student is suitable for vaccination.

This commit amends the 'Add' and 'Edit' command, 'Person' class and
other relevant classes and tests to support the use of the Medical
Details parameter. This commit also removes the 'Tag' parameter.

As life-threatening adverse drug reactions (ADRs) have been reported in
people with certain underlying medical conditions, knowing this will
help UHC staff determine who is suitable for vaccination and keep
everyone safe.

School Residence is an optional field that will be contained within a
Person object. It will be used to determine if a student stays on
campus. It is optional as most students do not stay on campus.

This commit amends the 'Add' and 'Edit' command, 'Person' class and
other relevant classes and tests to support the use of the School
Residence parameter.

As school residences tend to be densely populated, this field will allow
UHC staff determine if an outbreak is possible, and vaccinate students
before it happens.

The position of the SchoolResidence optional parameter has been shifted
to the end. This helps to prevent any user confusion regarding
optional parameters.

Previously, a ParseException would be thrown as the command was
not updated to check for Medical Details, Matriculation Number,
School Residence and Vaccination Status.

Faculty is one of the fields that will be
contained within a Person object. It will be used for
other functions later to filter students by faculty.

This commit amends the 'Add' and 'Edit' command, 'Person'
class and other relevant classes and tests to support
the use of the Faculty parameter.

Knowing the faculty information will give the faculties
more information on safe reopening, allow faculties to liaise
with their students directly, reducing the burden on UHC staff.
I had forgotten to check the code style.

Person.equals() and Person.toString() have been updated with the
new fields.

of strings.

to Command Summary.

commitResults.messageBody: Out-of-index inputs will now display the correct error message.
The failing tests will now pass following the most recent change.

For SchoolResidence and Faculty, the given input must be entirely in
capital letters.

The description of the undo/redo implementation is a legacy of the AB3
